main event: A silver object about 23 degrees above the horizon was observed for 3 minutes moving at high speed.
interesting points: The object was initially thought to be a balloon or satellite, but the duration of the sighting was consistent with an aircraft.
The observation did not indicate features of an aircraft, however, and the object was heavy monitoring this sector.
The case was considered as Insufficient Data.
The object was observed at coordinates 32.20N 172.00W in the Pacific Ocean.
The sighting occurred at 0555L on 7 FEB 1963.
